title.narrative: Output 3.1 Government and service providers have capacity to ensure children’s rights to live in a non-violent family environment

description.narrative: UNICEF played a key role in supporting the Child Code reform, which is currently undergoing parliamentary process. This reform encompasses amendments to 14 pieces of legislation, including the Criminal Code. The revision provides for the ban of corporal punishment and prohibition of placement of children in residential institution with more than 12 units. A total of 950 additional social workers were allocated by the Government to focus on the prevention and response to violence against children and the prevention of family separation. A digital database was set up to register and manage the cases of children in difficult life situation. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:27/01/2020
